From: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
Subject: [PATCH] ath11k: balance the AHB extended IRQ enable/disable pair

The firmware-crash recovery flow (QMI server exit ->
ath11k_core_pre_reconfigure_recovery -> restart) never disables the
extended DP interrupts, but ath11k_core_qmi_firmware_ready()
unconditionally re-enables them, so every crash recovery on the AHB bus
trips the depth check once per DP interrupt line - observed on IPQ8074
as a storm of 13 warnings per recovery pass:

  Unbalanced enable for IRQ 59
  WARNING: CPU: 2 PID: 11359 at kernel/irq/manage.c:774 __enable_irq
    ath11k_ahb_ext_irq_enable
    ath11k_core_qmi_firmware_ready
    ath11k_core_restart

Make the AHB ext_irq_enable/ext_irq_disable ops idempotent with the
ATH11K_FLAG_EXT_IRQ_ENABLED dev flag that the PCI(C) bus code already
maintains for the same purpose, so the pair stays balanced no matter
which recovery flow invokes it.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ahb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/ahb.c
@@ -393,6 +393,9 @@ static void ath11k_ahb_ext_irq_enable(st
 {
 	int i;
 
+	if (test_and_set_bit(ATH11K_FLAG_EXT_IRQ_ENABLED, &ab->dev_flags))
+		return;
+
 	for (i = 0; i < ATH11K_EXT_IRQ_GRP_NUM_MAX; i++) {
 		struct ath11k_ext_irq_grp *irq_grp = &ab->ext_irq_grp[i];
 
@@ -407,6 +410,9 @@ static void ath11k_ahb_ext_irq_enable(st
 
 static void ath11k_ahb_ext_irq_disable(struct ath11k_base *ab)
 {
+	if (!test_and_clear_bit(ATH11K_FLAG_EXT_IRQ_ENABLED, &ab->dev_flags))
+		return;
+
 	__ath11k_ahb_ext_irq_disable(ab);
 	ath11k_ahb_sync_ext_irqs(ab);
 }
